Many confusing operators certainly exist(especially in Control.Arrow), but the ones you have mentioned are the worst possible examples you could give. All of those have a clear meaning, and are extremely useful<p><pre><code>    f . g y . h z a . f&#x27;
</code></pre>
is certainly much clearer than<p><pre><code>    f `compose` g y `compose` h z a `compose` f&#x27;
</code></pre>
The same goes for (>>=)
